<subSubSection id="C31265278D21015C828EB62DEAF5FA5D" pageId="2" pageNumber="190" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB736AC8D21015C828EB62DED24FCE5" blockId="2.[151,1437,831,1864]" box="[151,830,831,856]" pageId="2" pageNumber="190">
<emphasis id="B97CEABE8D21015C828EB62DEF57FCE5" bold="true" box="[151,333,831,856]" pageId="2" pageNumber="190">Measurements.</emphasis>
Length. Male. 
<quantity id="4CF09B498D21015C83E0B62DEC66FCE5" box="[505,636,831,856]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.65" metricValueMax="5.9" metricValueMin="5.4" pageId="2" pageNumber="190" unit="mm" value="5.65" valueMax="5.9" valueMin="5.4">5.4–5.9mm</quantity>
; Female. 
<quantity id="4CF09B498D21015C80F1B62DED20FCE5" box="[744,826,831,856]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.7" pageId="2" pageNumber="190" unit="mm" value="6.7">6.7mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736AC8D21015C82DEB676EC9AFC55" blockId="2.[151,1437,831,1864]" pageId="2" pageNumber="190">Yellowish. Vertex, pronotum, scutellum and compound eyes silvery yellowish. Forewings yellow with irregular brownish spots in median area. Vertex and thorax with median longitudinal black stripe extending to second apical cell of forewings along with anterior margin of clavus, with even lateral margins; second apical cell with black spot, area around each spot pale.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736AC8D21015C82DEB6E6EB3EFB8D" blockId="2.[151,1437,831,1864]" pageId="2" pageNumber="190">Ocelli on vertex, just above and next to antennal bases. Vertex nearly equal or slightly narrower than pronotum, slightly longer than breadth between eyes. Pronotum about 1.7x as wide as long, shorter than scutellum.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736AC8D21015C82DEB12EEF6CFAED" blockId="2.[151,1437,831,1864]" pageId="2" pageNumber="190">
Male genitalia. Pygofer lobe bluntly conical at posterior margin, with macrosetae confined to posterior 0.33 area, with short spin-like process at ventral margin, about 
<date id="FFB6106C8D21015C815BB172ED44FBC5" box="[834,862,1120,1144]" pageId="2" pageNumber="190">2x</date>
longer than high, anal tube base with long basal process almost reaching ventral margin of pygofer. Subgenital plates long, narrowed apically, slightly broad at base, with irregular microsetae, about 
<date id="FFB6106C8D21015C8079B1B5EC66FB7D" box="[608,636,1191,1216]" pageId="2" pageNumber="190">5x</date>
longer than broad (basal width). Style with preapical lobe broadly rounded, apophysis long, slender, around ½ of total length, spine-like, narrowing towards apex. Connective “Y”- shaped, with stem longer than arms. Aedeagus with shaft curved laterally, apically directed cephalad, broad at apex with apical sclerotization of shaft, with membranous area and pair of subequal spines, basal processes of dorsal apodeme hook-like.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736AC8D21015C82DEB04EEAF5FA5D" blockId="2.[151,1437,831,1864]" pageId="2" pageNumber="190">
Female. Hind margin of seventh sternite medially notched in new species (
<figureCitation id="13332A298D21015C8607B04EEA79FAC8" box="[1054,1123,1372,1397]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1959,1981]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,226,1848]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,194,1935]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Nirvana spinosa sp. nov. 1. habitus, dorsal view; 2. pygofer lobe, lateral view; 3. connective, style and subgenital plates, dorsal view; 4. aedeagus, lateral view; 5. aedeagus, caudal view; 6. female seventh sternite, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458328/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="190">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). First valvulae (
<figureCitation id="13332A298D21015C873FB04EEB89FAC9" box="[1318,1427,1372,1397]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1198,1220]" captionTargetBox="[178,1405,201,1072]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,191,1176]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. Nirvana spinosa sp. nov. 7, 8. Valvula I, lateral view; 9, 10. Valvula II, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458330/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="190">Figs. 7, 8</figureCitation>
) concave dorsally and acute apically in lateral view, dorsal sculptured area extending from basal 2/3 to apex and ventral scale-like sculptured area restricted to apical portion. Second valvulae, in lateral view, tapering apically with serrations, dorsal margin with 12-14 teeth in apical half and a small tooth at base (
<figureCitation id="13332A298D21015C867EB0D5EAFBFA5D" box="[1127,1249,1479,1504]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="3.[151,258,1198,1220]" captionTargetBox="[178,1405,201,1072]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,191,1176]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. Nirvana spinosa sp. nov. 7, 8. Valvula I, lateral view; 9, 10. Valvula II, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1458330/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="190">Figs. 9, 10</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
